# Web conventions

## API access

All HTTP traffic goes through `src/lib/api.ts`. No `fetch(...)` or
`axios(...)` calls anywhere else in the codebase. This single seam is where
auth headers, `X-Clinic-Id`, and the global error model are normalised.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
const res = await fetch('/api/patients');

// ✅ GOOD
import { apiClient } from '@/lib/api';
const data = await apiClient.get<PatientPage>('/patients');
```

## Server state

- Read paths use `useQuery` from `@tanstack/react-query`.
- Writes use `useMutation`; on success, `invalidateQueries` (don't manually
  patch the cache unless you must).
- Keys are arrays starting with the resource: `['patients', { page }]`,
  `['patient', patientId]`.

## Routing

File-based routes under `src/routes/`. The TanStack Vite plugin regenerates
`src/routeTree.gen.ts` on save. Don't hand-edit unless you also touch the
matching route files.

## PHI

- Never put patient names, phone numbers, or other PHI in URL params, query
  strings, or analytics events.
- Avoid storing patient data in `localStorage`. Tokens + selected `clinic_id`
  are fine; patient rows are not.

## Components & styling

- Tailwind utility classes + `cn()` helper from `@/lib/cn`.
- Reusable bits go in `src/components/`. Pages live in `src/routes/`.
- Functional components only. Custom hooks for cross-component logic.
